An important function of CSNET is to simplify communication by electronic mail. To this end, a <i>Name Server</i> facility is being implemented, which will free users from having to understand the complexities of inter-network mail addressing. The Name Server includes a database and accessing software on a central <i>Service Host</i> machine, as well as programs and data structures on CSNET member hosts. We describe the architecture of the Name Server and discuss considerations that lead to its design.